      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "New & Highlighted Features Worth Your Attention",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "CloudTalk ships updates frequently — here are the ones I'm most excited about right now.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "AI Call Summaries",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "After each call, CloudTalk auto-generates a concise summary: who called, what was discussed, and what the next steps are. This lands directly in your CRM. Agents no longer waste 2–3 minutes typing notes after every conversation. Multiply that by 50 calls a day per agent, and you've recovered serious hours.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Smart Dialer with Lead Scoring",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The newest iteration of the power dialer doesn't just go through a list sequentially. It prioritizes leads based on score (pulled from your CRM fields like last email open, deal stage, or website activity). High-intent leads get called first. One e-commerce client saw a 22% lift in connect rates after turning this on.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "SMS & WhatsApp Messaging",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "CloudTalk isn't voice-only anymore. You can send and receive SMS and WhatsApp messages from the same interface. Agents toggle between channels without switching tabs. For support teams, this means customers reach you on the channel they prefer — and you keep everything logged in one place.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Improved Salesforce & HubSpot Integrations",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The latest integration updates sync call data, recordings, and AI summaries bi-directionally. Notes typed in CloudTalk appear in Salesforce within seconds. Contact records created in HubSpot show up in CloudTalk's dialer immediately. No more stale data.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l3",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/cloudtalk-new-features"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "For a full rundown of every recent release, bookmark our ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "CloudTalk new features",
            "marks": [
              "l3"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " page.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tips & Best Ways to Get the Most Out of CloudTalk",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Here's where I get specific. These are the practices that separate a team just *using* CloudTalk from a team that's *crushing it* with CloudTalk.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 1: Build Your IVR Around Caller Intent, Not Internal Org Charts",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Most companies design their IVR to mirror their departments: \"Press 1 for Sales, Press 2 for Support.\" That's fine, but it's not great. Instead, map your IVR to what callers actually want:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "\"Press 1 to check your order status.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "\"Press 2 to talk about pricing or upgrade your plan.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "\"Press 3 for everything else.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "CloudTalk's IVR builder lets you A/B test these flows. Run both versions for two weeks and compare abandonment rates. The intent-based version almost always wins.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 2: Use Tags and Disposition Codes Religiously",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "After every call, agents should tag it (e.g., \"Demo Scheduled,\" \"Pricing Inquiry,\" \"Churn Risk\") using CloudTalk's disposition codes. This turns your analytics dashboard from a vanity metric display into a genuine decision-making tool. When you can see that 30% of Monday morning calls are pricing inquiries, you staff differently.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 3: Set Up Automated Call Workflows",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "CloudTalk supports workflow automations. A few examples that work well:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Missed call → automatic SMS callback offer.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " If a call goes to voicemail, CloudTalk texts the caller: \"Sorry we missed you. Reply CALL and we'll ring you back in 5 minutes.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Post-call → CRM task creation.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " When an agent tags a call as \"Follow-up needed,\" CloudTalk creates a task in HubSpot or Salesforce automatically.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Long hold time → priority routing.",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " If a caller has been waiting over 90 seconds, bump them to the next available senior agent.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ],
        "listItem": "bullet",
        "level": 1
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 4: Leverage AI Scoring for Coaching, Not Punishment",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "CloudTalk's AI scores calls on parameters like talk-to-listen ratio, sentiment, and script adherence. The best managers I've seen use these scores as coaching springboards, not report cards. Pull up a 6/10 call during a one-on-one and ask the agent: \"What do you think happened at the 3-minute mark?\" It sparks self-reflection far better than a top-down critique.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 5: Integrate Deeply, Don't Just Connect",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l4",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-clickup"
          },
          {
            "_key": "l5",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/how-to-use-monday-com"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A shallow integration means calls log in your CRM. A deep integration means call data *changes how you work*. Connect CloudTalk to your helpdesk (Zendesk, Freshdesk), your CRM, your project management tool, and even your email platform. If you're running complex workflows, pairing CloudTalk with tools like ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "ClickUp",
            "marks": [
              "l4"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " or ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "monday.com",
            "marks": [
              "l5"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " can turn phone insights into project tasks automatically.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Tip 6: Use Number Masking for Privacy-Compliant Outbound",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If your team calls customers on behalf of partners or marketplaces, CloudTalk's number masking keeps personal numbers hidden. It's a small feature that prevents big compliance headaches.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
